From ff3fea4fbab5abf0b88ed83d62254e4b104e08d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dylan Marma <dylan@requitygroup.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 18:42:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Deprecate card types in favor of conditions engine for
 pipeline field resolution

Replace unified_card_types with the two-axis visibility conditions engine
(asset_class x loan_type) as the single source of truth for which fields,
UW outputs, and card metrics appear on pipeline deals.

- Rewrite NewDealDialog to use Capital Side + Loan Type instead of CardTypeSelector
- Replace card type filter with loan type filter in DealFilters
- DealDetailPage uses useConditionDrivenFields + useDealConfig hooks
- Add useConditionDrivenFields hook (fetches field_configurations by visibility)
- Add useDealConfig hook (matches deal_config_templates by conditions scoring)
- Make card_type_id nullable on unified_deals, add loan_type column
- Fix visibility engine: multifamily/mhc classified as Commercial
- Document extraction API works with conditions engine fields
- Backward-compatible synthetic cardType for child components

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
