+# Card Types Deprecation - Context
+
+## Objective
+Replace the unified_card_types system with the conditions engine (field_configurations visibility conditions) as the single source of truth for determining which fields appear on pipeline deals.
+
+## Key Decisions
+
+### Two-axis conditions engine replaces card type selection
+- Asset Class (Residential/Commercial) x Loan Type (Bridge/DSCR/Perm/Construction/Equity) determines which fields show
+- Each field's own `visibility_condition` in `field_configurations` determines visibility
+- No more "selecting a card type" when creating deals
+
+### New deal creation flow
+- Step 1: Capital Side (Debt/Equity) + Loan Type selection
+- Step 2: Asset Class selection
+- Step 3: Deal details (name, amount, date, assignee)
+- No more CardTypeSelector component
+
+### deal_config_templates table provides uw_outputs/card_metrics
+- Created in prior session, keyed by asset_class_condition + loan_type_condition
+- Replaces uw_outputs and card_metrics that lived on card types
+- useDealConfig hook fetches and matches by conditions
+
+### Synthetic cardType for backward compatibility
+- DealDetailPage constructs a synthetic UnifiedCardType object from conditions-driven data
+- Child components (PropertyTab, ContactsTab, UnderwritingPanel) still receive cardType prop
+- No changes needed to child components yet
+
+## Completed Changes
+
+### Database
+- `unified_deals.card_type_id` made nullable
+- `unified_deals.loan_type` column added (text)
+- `deal_config_templates` table created (prior session)
+- field_configurations visibility_condition backfilled for 50 fields (prior session)
+- loan_type backfilled on all 23 active deals from card type slug mapping
+
+### Files Modified
+- `components/pipeline-v2/NewDealDialog.tsx` - Rewrote to use Capital Side + Loan Type instead of CardTypeSelector
+- `components/pipeline-v2/DealFilters.tsx` - Replaced card type filter with loan type filter
+- `components/pipeline-v2/PipelineView.tsx` - cardTypes prop optional, filter by loan_type
+- `components/pipeline-v2/pipeline-types.ts` - card_type_id nullable, added loan_type
+- `app/(authenticated)/admin/pipeline-v2/actions.ts` - card_type_id optional, accepts loan_type
+- `app/api/deals/extract-from-document/route.ts` - Works with conditions engine fields instead of card type
+- `app/(authenticated)/admin/pipeline-v2/[id]/page.tsx` - Card type fetch conditional
+- `app/(authenticated)/admin/pipeline-v2/[id]/DealDetailPage.tsx` - Uses useConditionDrivenFields + useDealConfig
+- `hooks/useConditionDrivenFields.ts` - New hook (prior session)
+- `hooks/useDealConfig.ts` - New hook (prior session)
+
+### Files NOT Changed (still reference card types for backward compat)
+- `components/pipeline-v2/PipelineKanban.tsx` - Uses cardTypeMap for display labels
+- `components/pipeline-v2/PipelineTable.tsx` - Uses cardTypeMap for display labels
+- Pipeline list page still fetches card types (for label display on existing deals)
+- Card type admin pages still exist but can be removed in future cleanup
+
+## Gotchas
+- Generated Supabase types still have card_type_id as non-nullable; used Omit override in actions.ts
+- LOAN_TYPES enum in visibility-engine.ts matches what the new deal dialog presents
+- Existing deals with card_type_id continue to work; new deals created without one
+
+## Last Updated: 2026-03-12
+## Next Steps:
+- Optional: Remove card type admin pages
+- Optional: Remove CardTypeSelector component and NewDealSheet (dead code)
+- Optional: Regenerate Supabase types to reflect nullable card_type_id
